Female, adult
(
holotype
; 
Fig. 3A–C
)

ABDOMEN (
Fig. 6A–C
). Tergites and sternites undivided, tergal chaetotaxy 6:6:7:8:8:8:8:7:7:6:6:2; sternal chaetotaxy 10:10:7:9:8:8:8:8:6:4:2; pleural membrane granulate anteriorly near cephalothorax, granulo-striate posteriorly; without setae.

GENITALIA (
Fig. 8E
). Setae arranged linearly in two rows 2:6 on sternite 2 and 8 setae arranged linearly on sternite 3 below opening.

LEGS (
Fig. 7A–B
). All legs with tarsus longer than metatarsus; scarcely granulate; femur + patella of leg IV 2.47 times as long as broad; legs III and IV with articulation between femur and patella segments slightly oblique; tibiae III and IV and metatarsi III and IV with tactile setae; tarsi of legs III and IV with tactile setae sub-basally; arolium shorter than claws, distally broadened and undivided; claws simple and not serrate.

Male, adult
(
allotype
; 
Fig. 4A–C
)

GENITALIA (
Fig. 8D
). Setae arranged linearly around small rounded ejaculatory opening; 2:4 setae above and 2:2:8 setae arranged linearly under ejaculatory opening.
